full_text: @gcaw @JohnsHopkins My eldest fell into the category "average excellent" (4.0+, 35 ACT, lots of AP classes). I'd rather she have a couple of all-state caliber athletes as classmates than more vanilla "scholars". The world of dedication and achievement is more diverse than that.
user.name: David Ryan
user.description: Bus driver, ship captain, and student pilot.

full_text: @gcaw @JohnsHopkins Yes, I understand that as tbe process works right now there are exclusive carve outs for athletes. My question is do you personally see athletic excellence as fundamentally different from other expressions of excellence not measured by the SAT? I don't.
user.name: David Ryan

full_text: @Yascha_Mounk @JRubinBlogger @JohnsHopkins @Harvard @Princeton @Yale I had no idea this was still done! Every student should get in on merit alone, not who their parents were.
